title: Starship Explosion a Setback, But Not a Total Failure For SpaceX and Musk
description: The first flight of the most powerful rocket ever was not the success that Elon Musk and his company hoped for, but the launch achieved several milestones toward future journeys.

title: Twitter Begins Removing Blue Check Marks From Verified Accounts
description: Elon Musk, the owner of the social media service, has begun to charge a subscription fee for the verification symbol.

title: Florida Apologizes After 4:45 A.M. Emergency Alert Test
description: The Florida Division of Emergency Management said the early morning alert was not supposed to disturb people who were asleep.

title: Peering Into the Future of Novels, With the Help of AI
description: Who wrote it, the novelist or the technology? How about both? Stephen Marche experiments with teaching artificial intelligence to write with him, not for him.

title: Electric Vehicle Tax Credit Rules Create ‘Chaos for Consumers’
description: Buying an electric car has become much more complicated because of restrictions on which models qualify for a federal tax credit of up to $7,500.
